# Implementation Review: eden-phase-9d-evaluator-module

## Plan

- Path: `/Users/ericalt/Documents/eden/docs/plans/eden-phase-9d-evaluator-module.md`
- Summary: Add the evaluator role to the reference Web UI as the
  fourth chunk of Phase 9. Adds `/evaluator/*` routes mounted
  unconditionally (no CLI flag), with claim → draft → submit
  walking `store.submit` with retry-before-orphan + read-back.
  Differs from chunk 9c in three ways: no git work; trial pre-
  exists; status has three values; `IllegalTransition` falls
  through to read-back rather than short-circuiting.

## Implementation Files

| File | Action | Plan Section |
|---|---|---|
| `reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/evaluator.py` | Created | §A New routes module + §C Request flow |
| `reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/_helpers.py` | Modified — extracted `_read_inline_artifact`, added `read_trial_artifact` | §A.1 Artifact trust boundary (helper generalization) |
| `reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/forms.py` | Modified — added `EvaluateDraft` + `parse_evaluate_form` + `_parse_metric_value` | §B Forms helper |
| `reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/app.py` | Modified — included `evaluator_routes.router` unconditionally | §F CLI |
| `reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/templates/base.html` | Modified — permanent navigation link | §D Templates |
| `reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/templates/evaluator_list.html` | Created | §D Templates |
| `reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/templates/evaluator_claim.html` | Created | §D Templates |
| `reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/templates/evaluator_submitted.html` | Created | §D Templates |
| `reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/templates/evaluator_orphaned.html` | Created | §D Templates |
| `reference/services/web-ui/tests/conftest.py` | Modified — added `seed_evaluate_task` + `get_evaluate_submission` helpers | §I.test-fixture additions |
| `reference/services/web-ui/tests/test_evaluator_routes.py` | Created | §I.1 |
| `reference/services/web-ui/tests/test_evaluator_flow.py` | Created | §I.2 |
| `reference/services/web-ui/tests/test_evaluator_partial_write.py` | Created | §I.3 |
| `reference/services/web-ui/tests/test_evaluator_security.py` | Created | §I.4 |
| `reference/services/web-ui/tests/test_evaluator_e2e.py` | Created | §I.5 |
| `CLAUDE.md` (the project AGENTS.md) | Modified — phase-status block | §G Docs |
| `reference/README.md` | Modified | §G Docs |
| `reference/services/web-ui/README.md` | Modified — evaluator-module section | §G Docs |
| `docs/roadmap.md` | Modified — 9d marked complete | §G Docs |

## Change Summary

- Added the evaluator module under `/evaluator/*` (list / claim /
  draft / submit), mounted unconditionally; the trial_id is
  read from `task.payload.trial_id` at claim time and stashed in
  an in-process `_CLAIMS` dict (per-(csrf, task_id) isolation).
- Generalized the chunk-9c `read_proposal_rationale` trust
  boundary into `_read_inline_artifact(uri, artifacts_dir)` and
  added `read_trial_artifact` for the trial-side surface.
  `read_proposal_rationale` is now a thin wrapper.
- New `parse_evaluate_form` validates per-metric types per the
  spec (`integer` accepts wire-legal `1.0`, `real` rejects non-
  finite, text non-empty after strip, `success` requires ≥ 1
  metric), with closed-set status validation and accumulated
  per-field errors.
- `_retry_submit_with_readback` differs from chunk 9c: `WrongToken`
  / `ConflictingResubmission` short-circuit; `InvalidPrecondition`
  re-renders the form (fixable); `IllegalTransition` and other
  transport-shaped exceptions feed the read-back arm. The read-
  back uses `read_task` + `read_submission` +
  `submissions_equivalent` to distinguish "we won, response
  lost" from "lost the race" from "claim still ours".
- 56 new tests (20 routes + 5 flow + 12 partial-write recovery +
  18 security + 1 e2e). Full suite: 553 unit + 5 e2e green.

## Review Status

Round 0 — awaiting initial review.

## Round 1 — fixes

- **Bug fixed.** [evaluator.py:218–238](reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/evaluator.py): the submit handler now collects every submitted `metric.*` field (not just declared schema keys) and forwards them all to `parse_evaluate_form`, so a hand-crafted POST with `metric.ghost` is rejected. Default declared keys to `""` so the parser still sees blanks for the omit-on-empty branch. Companion change in [forms.py](reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/forms.py): unknown keys surface as `add_overall(...)` rather than `add(0, name, ...)` so the rejection appears on the rendered form (the field doesn't exist on the page to render an inline error against).
- **Risk fixed.** Read paths in [evaluator.py](reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/evaluator.py): `list_pending` (L82-87), `claim` (L114-122), `draft_form` (L156-162), and `submit` pre-reads (L213-219) now also catch transport-shaped `Exception` (the StoreClient surface) and route them through the existing wire-error UX (banner / 502) instead of letting them surface as 500.
- **Risk fixed.** [test_evaluator_routes.py:243-264](reference/services/web-ui/tests/test_evaluator_routes.py): the unknown-metric-key test now drives the actual route via a hand-crafted POST that includes both `metric.score` and `metric.ghost` and asserts the 400 + "not in schema" banner. The previous parser-direct test is gone.
- **Nit fixed.** [evaluator_claim.html](reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/templates/evaluator_claim.html): added an `{% else %}` branch under the proposal-rationale block so the operator sees a "rationale not rendered inline" note when the artifact is outside the trust envelope.

Verification: `uv run ruff check .` clean; `uv run pyright` clean; `uv run pytest -q` 553 passed; `uv run pytest -m e2e` 5 passed (chunk-9d e2e included).

## Round 2 — fixes

- **Risk fixed.** [evaluator.py:139-149](reference/services/web-ui/src/eden_web_ui/routes/evaluator.py): `store.claim` now also catches transport-shaped `Exception` and surfaces the wire-error UX (303 + `?banner=task-store+transport+failure:+<class>`) instead of letting it surface as 500. Added [`test_claim_transport_failure_surfaces_banner`](reference/services/web-ui/tests/test_evaluator_routes.py) — monkeypatches `store.claim` to raise and asserts the 303 + banner.

